WeRateDogs Report: A Data Wrangling Project by Akoh John¶

The verdict is in, we love puppos and puppers, it might be ambigous but that's fine depending on how you look at it, the most important thing is that these dogs are loved. So what's WeRateDogs about; WeRateDogs is a Twitter account that rates people's dogs with a humorous comment about the dog. These ratings almost always have a denominator of 10. The numerators, though? Almost always greater than 10. 11/10, 12/10, 13/10, etc. Why? Because "they're good dogs Brent." WeRateDogs has over 4 million followers and has received international media coverage. To find out what the furr is all about, we will be gathering it's data through a variety of sources.¶

So now that we know what WeRateDogs is all about, let's see what insights it's data might reveal to us. Upon careful analysis of these datasets, I reached some conclusions and genrate valuable insights. I began my analysis by researching the frequency distribution of variables in this dataset after Practical assessment and neccessary data cleaning exercise.¶

Looking at the rating distribution we can see that majority of the dogs in the dataset had relatively high ratings.

What dog stages are the most adored: On avergae the dog breeds at puppo stage seems to be getting majority of the likes and retweets, just incase you're wondering, the puppo stage is just like an adolescent, and despite having less repesentation in the dataset, it edges out the competition in the likes & retweets department; the Puppo stage leads Doggo stage by a slim margin having an average of (7183.700000 retweets and 23585 likes while the doggo stage has an average of (7364 retweets and 20153 likes), it doesn't get as close as this. The pupper dog stage had the total number of likes and retweets, which stood at 1647622 likes and retweets with a count of 150 entries.¶

Now let's take a look at the dependent variable which is ratings, it will be fascinating to know the cream of the top in this regards, considering that WeRateDogs view most dogs as 10s out of 10.

the chart above tells us that the Saluki breed is much rated above the other breeds with an avergae ratings of 12.5, despite the Golden retriever being the most re-occuring breed with a count of 139, while the Saluki breed only appeared 4 times in the data set, it might be due to it's dog stage, we might also consider that a certain dog breed can exist at different stages.¶

So let's take a look at the most adorable (likes & retweets) breeds at each dog stage, Keeping in mind that Puppo is the most adored dog stage on on average.¶

From the above we observe that at the Puppo stage, the lakeland terrier has the highest total likes at 132810, making it the most liked breed in the entire dataset.

Looking at the Time series plot of retweets and likes, we can observe that WeRateDogs has continued to garner social media engagement consistently over the two year period having the larger part of 2016 as its best moments; and with an ever increasing following, this trend is likely to continue.¶

Conclusion:¶

In Conclusion, to draw meaningful insights the data set has to be analysed critically and by doing so you end up with varying results. the results differ according to the method of aggregation which is to be expected.¶

Insights:¶

1.Firstly, there exist a positive correlation between likes and retweets, as retweets increase so does likes. this makes sense since more retweets mean increased visibility, audience approval and higher ratings.¶

2.Much of the total number of likes were shared among dogs breeds at the pupper stage but on avergae more likes, retweets and adoration went to dog breeds at the puppo stage.¶

3.From the time series chart, we can see that the most interactions occured within the period from 2016-06 to 2017-01 followed by a decline in engagement towards the period from 2017-07 to 2017-09, giving us an insight into whih period recorded the most ativity.¶
